import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="width", y="values", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.axhline(data['values'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['values'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of volcano eruption values based on their width?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
